  <teaser>Access to health, quality education, and decent work are among the Sustainable Development Goals established by the UN member states in 2015. A key indicator for these dimensions is the development of social skills. For populations with deficits in social interaction...</teaser>
  <objective><![CDATA[Access to health, quality education, and decent work are among the Sustainable Development Goals established by the UN member states in 2015. A key indicator for these dimensions is the development of social skills. For populations with deficits in social interaction, developing social skills is an ongoing and necessary task to ensure the well-being and social inclusion. EMOFACE offers a solution with high social impact, linking artificial intelligence technology and social skills development.

EMOFACE is developing applications and training services to support autistic people throughout their lives. Our first application, Emoface Play&Learn Emotions, proposes playful activities in interaction with 3D avatars in order to train socio-emotional skills such as: recognizing the emotions of others out of and in context, expressing and managing emotions, and understanding the intentions of others.

The curriculum and visual content used to illustrate emotions and social situations are adaptable to the users' needs so that our tools can accompany autistic people independently of their development and age. Our adapted design has been tested on non-verbal kids to adult autists with or without intellectual deficits. Our tools address both families and health practitioners, allowing them to easily share information about the improvement in socio-emotional skills, using our methodology that proposes objective measures in order to facilitate skill evaluation and even pre-diagnosis.

Women TechEU program can help respond to the biggest challenges faced by EMOFACE in short and mid-term. The activities I plan to support with the EU grant involve operational and strategic activities in relation to international development and validation of pathway to reimbursement plans. The program would also benefit coaching from international mentors with various expertise and the access to networks of expertise for growth and expansion to international markets and busi]]></objective>
